headlines.title: Trump says Musk will face 'serious consequences' if he funds Democratic candidates
headlines.description: Trump said there would be “serious consequences” if Elon Musk funds Democratic candidates to run against Republicans.

headlines.title: French Open 2025: Coco Gauff beats Aryna Sabalenka to win first Roland Garros title
headlines.description: Coco Gauff wins the first French Open singles title of her career by fighting back to beat world number one Aryna Sabalenka in a rollercoaster final.

headlines.title: Elon appears to delete X posts
headlines.description: It's the latest twist in the public spat between Elon Musk and President Donald Trump that escalated this week.

headlines.title: Eggs sold at Arizona Walmarts recalled for possible salmonella contamination
headlines.description: A California company is recalling nearly 2 million dozens of eggs after possibly being contaminated with Salmonella.

headlines.title: Israel says it has retrieved the body of a Thai hostage in Gaza
headlines.description: Israel said it had retrieved the body of Nattapong Pinta, who was abducted during the Oct. 7, 2023, attack that sparked the war. He had come to Israel to work in agriculture.

headlines.title: 'Ballerina' Opening Day at $10.6 Million, 'Stitch' on Top
headlines.description: 'Ballerina,' the 'John Wick' spinoff with Ana de Armas, earned a $10.6 million opening day at the box office, with 'Lilo & Stitch' still topping charts.

headlines.title: Sam Nivola and Cooper Koch on Nepo Babies, Incest and The White Lotus
headlines.description: Sam Nivola and Cooper Koch join Variety's 'Actors on Actors' to discuss their shows about complicated siblings.

headlines.title: Resident Evil Requiem Is Capcom's Next Horror Epic, Launches On Xbox In February 2026
headlines.description: RE9 has been announced! - Summer Game Fest 2025 has just closed out with the announcement of Capcom's Resident Evil Requiem — the next mainline entry in it...

headlines.title: Kilmar Abrego Garcia Returned to U.S. From El Salvador to Face Criminal Charges
headlines.description: Kilmar Armando Abrego Garcia, who had been living in Maryland and legally protected from deportation, had been held in a Salvadoran prison since March 15.

headlines.title: Aaron Rodgers arrives in Pittsburgh to sign contract with Steelers
headlines.description: Rodgers is officially signing his contract at the Steelers' facility today.
